erence for law-and-order enforcement, but low agreeableness and a competitive-jungle worldview create ambivalence about giving platforms too much power.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"leaf\": \"Public_Service_Broadcasting_Funding_Support\",\n      \"score\": 487,\n      \"confidence\": 0.65,\n      \"reasoning\": \"Very high trust in government and institutions (86% mean) aligns with funding public broadcasting, while moderate economic conservatism on welfare (6.49) tempers the enthusiasm, landing in clear support.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"leaf\": \"Recommender_System_Choice_Mandate_Support\",\n      \"score\": -132,\n      \"confidence\": 0.49,\n      \"reasoning\": \"Low openness and high authoritarian submission make the idea of individual algorithmic choice feel like an unnecessary burden, but very high openness to new experiences and ideas balances it into mild opposition.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"leaf\": \"Synthetic_Media_Labelling_Mandate_Support\",\n      \"score\": 531,\n      \"confidence\": 0.67,\n      \"reasoning\": \"High authoritarian preference for order and control, plus high trust in science/experts (90%), strongly support labeling to manage synthetic media, though low agreeableness prevents maximal endorsement.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"leaf\": \"Trust_In_Mainstream_Journalism\",\n      \"score\": -422,\n      \"confidence\": 0.71,\n      \"reasoning\": \"Very low agreeableness-trust (17%) and moderate anti-elitism (28%) together produce clear distrust of mainstream journalism, despite high trust in other institutional pillars.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"leaf\": \"Whistleblower_Protections_For_Platform_Researchers_Support\",\n      \"score\": 95,\n      \"confidence\": 0.43,\n      \"reasoning\": \"Very low altruism and tender-mindedness (both <7%) make protecting vulnerable individuals less appealing, while moderate openness to new ideas keeps the score barely above neutral.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"leaf\": \"Foreign_Information_Manipulation_Transparency_Mandate_Support\",\n      \"score\": 473,\n      \"confidence\": 0.64,\n      \"reasoning\": \"High national superiority beliefs and ethnic nationalism, paired with high trust in government, produce clear support for a mandate targeting foreign influence, moderated by a cosmopolitan orientation (75%).\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"leaf\": \"Government_Distrust_Of_Elections\",\n      \"score\": -284,\n      \"confidence\": 0.68,\n      \"reasoning\": \"Very high trust in government institutions (87%) and trust in judiciary (96%) make distrust of elections feel unfounded, creating mild opposition despite low general trust in people.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}",
